@{
    ViewBag.Title = "JustGiving QA Automation Recruitment";
}
@section featured {
    <section class="featured">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
            <hgroup class="title">
                <h1>@ViewBag.Title</h1>
            </hgroup>
            <p>
                These exercises are designed to assess your ability to create automated tests using SpecFlow (BDD), Selenium WebDriver, C# and NUnit.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>
}
<h3>You will need to automate ALL exercises using the following:</h3>
<ul>
    <li>SpecFlow (Gherkin Syntax)</li>
    <li>Selenium WebDriver</li>
    <li>Page Object Model</li>
    <li>C# and NUnit</li>
    <li>Visual Studio</li>
</ul>

<ol class="round">
    <li class="one">
        <h5>Exercise 1</h5>
        This exercise will assess your ability to create an automated test using SpecFlow, Selenium WebDriver, Page Object Model and C#
        
        <h6>Exercise Requirements</h6>
        <ol>
            <li>Start <a href=@Url.Action("Register", "Account")><strong>Exercise 1</strong></a></li> 
            <li>Register <strong>2</strong> new user accounts using <strong>1</strong> SpecFlow feature file and scenario.</li>
            <li>Verify the user is logged in.</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

    <li class="two">
        <h5>Exercise 2</h5>
        This exercise will assess your ability to automate an API using SpecFlow and C#
        
        <h6>Exercise Requirements</h6>
        <ol>
            <li>Call this <a href="api/exercise2"><strong>API</strong></a></li>
            <li>Parse the response.</li>
            <li>Output each donation amount to the console.</li>
            <li>Calculate and output the <strong>total sum</strong> of <strong>all</strong> donation amounts to the console.</li>
        </ol>

    </li>

    <li class="three">
        <h5>Exercise 3</h5>
        This exercise will assess your ability to locate and manipulate DOM elements.
        
        <h6>Exercise Requirements</h6>
        <ol>
            <li>Start <a href="/exercise3" id="exercise3"><strong>Exercise 3</strong></a></li>
            <li>Click the row number where row description is <strong>JustGiving</strong></li>
            <li>Verify that the opened page contains the message <strong>Well done, you opened the right link!</strong></li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    
    <li class="four">
        <h5>Finally</h5>
        <p>Please upload your completed solution to <a href="http://www.dropbox.com">Dropbox</a> and email the shared link to <a href="mailto:shashi@justgiving.com">shashi@justgiving.com</a> with subject <strong>QA Automation Recruitment Test</strong></p>
    </li>
</ol>
